  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN194.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">paruvaṅ kaṇṭu āṟṟāmai mītūrat talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What SHE said in order to subdue [her] lack of strength upon seeing the season.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN194.2">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>pēruṟai talaiiya perumpular vaikaṟai</l>
        <l>yēriṭam paṭutta virumaṟup pūḻip</l>
        <l>puṟamāṟu peṟṟa pūva līrat</l>
        <l>tūṉkiḻit taṉṉa ceñcuvar neṭuñcāl</l>
        <l>vittiya maruṅkiṉ vitaipala nāṟi</l>
        <l>yiralai naṉmā ṉiṉamparan tavaipōṟ</l>
        <l>kōṭuṭait talaikkuṭai cūṭiya viḷaiñar</l>
        <l>kaṟaṅkupaṟaic cīri ṉiraṅka vāṅkik</l>
        <l>kaḷaikkāl kaḻīiya perumpuṉa varakiṉ</l>
        <l>kavaikkati rirumpuṟaṅ katūu vuṇṭa</l>
        <l>kuṭumi neṟṟi neṭumāt tōkai</l>
        <l>kāmar kalavam parappi yēmuṟak</l>
        <l>kollai yuḻavar kāṭuḻa voḻitta</l>
        <l>vallilaik kuruntiṉ vāṅkuciṉai yiruntu</l>
        <l>kiḷikaṭi makaḷiriṉ viḷipaṭap payiruṅ</l>
        <l>kārma ṉikuḷai tōḻi pōrmikak</l>
        <l>koṭuñci neṭuntēr pūṇṭa kaṭumpari</l>
        <l>viriyuḷai naṉmā kaṭai<supplied>i</supplied></l>
        <l>varutu meṉṟavar teḷitta pōḻtē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>It [is] rainy season indeed, friend, [my] friend, (16a-c)</l>
        <l>when they call out so that shouts fall like [those of] women chasing parakeets, (15)</l>
        <l>perched on the bent branches of the lime tree with strong leaves (14)</l>
        <l>that was omitted when ploughing the wilderness by the ploughmen in the clearing, (13)</l>
        <l>delightfully spreading out [their] desirable feathers, (12)</l>
        <l>the long dark peacocks with crested foreheads (11)</l>
        <l>that had seized [and] eaten the big backs of forked ears (10)</l>
        <l>on the millet in the vast field from which the [old] stalks had been removed by weeding, (8)</l>
        <l>the harvest men who wore baskets on [their] bowed heads (6)</l>
        <l>pulling [at them], while the resounding drums sound like a song, (7)</l>
        <l>resembling a group of fine Iralai stags that is scattered, (6)</l>
        <l>smelling of the many seeds on the side that has been sown, (5)</l>
        <l>in the long furrow with a wall red like torn meat, (4)</l>
        <l>in the wetness of the red earth that had undergone a great transformation (3)</l>
        <l>from the dark stained dust brought under control by the plough, (2)</l>
        <l>at great dawning dawn that had showered big drops [of rain]. (1)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
